HEADWORD: cryometer
<hw>cry*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ cold,
frost + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A
thermometer for the measurement of low temperatures, esp. such an
instrument containing alcohol or some other liquid of a lower freezing
point than mercury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

